<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="834" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg" data-orig-size="1024,768" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="Air Koryo&#8217;s Ilyushin Il-62" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-834" alt="Air Koryo's Ilyushin Il-62" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=490&#038;h=367" width="490" height="367" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=490&amp;h=367 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=980&amp;h=734 980w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryos-ilyushin-il-62.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>B y 2010, it appeared airline frequent flyers were getting used to bland fare:</p>
<p>Route:         Pyongyang to Beijing, 2009-09-10</p>
<p>Date added:          2010-05-08</p>
<p>Flight duration:    2h 0m</p>
<p>Flight class:          business</p>
<p>Ticket price:</p>
<p>Aircraft:      TU154</p>
<p>Meal:          Airkoryo.jpg Typical Korean (North) meal&#8230;</p>
<p>Drink:         &#8220;Orange Drink with Pulp&#8221; (their words)</p>
<p>Comments:           Airkoryo3.jpg &#8211; Blanched peanuts and &#8220;Orange Drink with Pulp&#8221;</p>
<p>On the aviation forum airliners.net, which bills itself as the wings of the web”, Gialloboy from Ireland posted on September 3, 2012 on his trip from Beijing to Pyongyang. “Woke up Tuesday morning with a rather bad hangover but managed to drag myself in the shower and ultimately into a cab to Beijing airport. Traffic was not too bad for a change and I arrived in Terminal 2 within 30 minutes. Did some last minute email (no Internet in the DPRK!) and drank some Isotonic drinks which made me feel a lot better.” The Irish lad offered copious detail for the frequent Pyongyang flyers that were to follow him. “Terminal 2 is nothing special and get&#8217;s a lot of flights to obscure places, including 2 Air Koryo flights to FNJ (Air China flies to FNJ from Terminal 2 by the way)”</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="828" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/koryo4/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg" data-orig-size="400,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="koryo4" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg?w=400" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-828" alt="koryo4" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg?w=490" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg 400w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg?w=150 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/koryo4.jpg?w=300 300w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"   /></a></p>
<p>“At 11 am I made my way past security and on towards Air Koryo&#8217;s check in. They actually have a separate J checkin and I had my boarding card and lounge pass within 60 seconds. Funny thing is that Korean Air operates check in desks for their flight to Seoul in the very next row of desks! Check in desk (used for J PAX). Went past immigration and visited the lounge. Air Koryo uses the Air China lounge which is again used by Korean Air! ”</p>
<p>“Boarded quickly and settled into my comfy J seat. There are three rows in a 2-2 configuration; I was in row 2 and next to a quite friendly Danish businessman. We had some good conversation about his frequent trips to Pyongyang.</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="857" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg" data-orig-size="590,443" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-857" alt="the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=490&#038;h=367" width="490" height="367" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=490&amp;h=367 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/the-seatbelt-sign-is-old-school.jpg 590w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>Unfortunately photos are not allowed inside Air Koryo planes so all shots are &#8220;sneaked&#8221;, the Danish businessman acted as my &#8220;wingman&#8221; and kept an eye on the FAs. There had been cases of travelers made to delete all of their pictures so I was extra careful. Air Koryo J class snaps, rather stylish and nice. I have no idea why they score only 1 star on Skytrax, I thought they were rather adequate for a 2 hour flight and probably offered more comfort than some US airlines.”</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="842" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg" data-orig-size="590,443" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-842" alt="but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=490&#038;h=367" width="490" height="367" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=490&amp;h=367 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/but-see-all-that-smoke-its-water-vapor-coming-from-the-air-conditioning-outlets-explained-fahey-on-flickr-it-was-as-if-they-had-a-fog-machine-running-in-the-cabin.jpg 590w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>“Despite the flight being only 120 minutes we got a full meal, consisting of cold cuts and curry. Not bad at all! drinks were served also with a choice of water, soft drink and beer. Meal was followed by coffee. Note there was no milk, as everywhere in North Korea. Only powdered cream. FA consisted of a patriotic North Korean film: Thanks were paid to the Great Leader when we entered DPRK airspace and shortly after we touched down in FNJ. Surely this airport has one of the longest taxies anywhere in the world.</p>
<p>The TU204 at home base in FNJ”</p>
<p>Then the Irishman landed in Pyongyang.</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="830" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/1-6/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg" data-orig-size="1024,578" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="1-6" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-830" alt="1-6" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=490&#038;h=276" width="490" height="276" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=490&amp;h=276 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=978&amp;h=552 978w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=150&amp;h=85 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=300&amp;h=169 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/1-6.jpg?w=768&amp;h=434 768w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>“Arrivals is pretty new, the old Soviet style terminal has been bulldozed to the ground. We were in within 30 minutes and they had our mobile phonesJ.”</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="841" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/busy-day-in-fnj/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg" data-orig-size="799,599" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;3.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;DSC-HX5V&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1345534892&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.2&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;640&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.033333333333333&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="Busy day in FNJ!" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-841" alt="Busy day in FNJ!" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=490&#038;h=367" width="490" height="367" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=490&amp;h=367 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=150&amp;h=112 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/busy-day-in-fnj.jpg 799w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>Busy day in FNJ!</p>
<p>Into town and first stop Arch of Triumph: People were training for the upcoming torch parade on Kim Il Sung square</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="836" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg" data-orig-size="590,443" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-836" alt="air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=490&#038;h=367" width="490" height="367" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=490&amp;h=367 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/air-koryo-actually-hasnt-had-an-incident-since-2006-when-a-plane-ran-off-a-runway-and-hasnt-had-any-fatalities-since-1983.jpg 590w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>The Irishman had a few comments on the discussion board: “Quoting theobcman (Reply 5):</p>
<p>“Also when you say they took your mobile phones at the airport, then what happens? Do they keep them until your return flight?”</p>
<p>He replied “You get the phone back when you are about to leave the country.”</p>
<p>Another intrepid traveler inquired “Is milk is not available in DPRK at all?”</p>
<p><a href="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="832" data-permalink="https://natethayer.wordpress.com/2013/01/26/frequent-flyers-guide-to-north-korean-air-a-review-of-worlds-only-one-star-airline/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang/" data-orig-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg" data-orig-size="719,528" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=490" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-832" alt="139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang" src="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=490&#038;h=359" width="490" height="359" srcset="https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=490&amp;h=359 490w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=150&amp;h=110 150w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg?w=300&amp;h=220 300w, https://natethayer.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/139287-north-korea-s-flagship-airline-air-koryo-to-pyongyang.jpg 719w" sizes="(max-width: 490px) 100vw, 490px" /></a></p>
<p>Our Celtic correspondent helpfully explained “Not really, if anything else most Asians are lactose intolerant so there is not much of a demand for milk to begin with. Second dairy is very resource intensive to make, something the DPRK does not have a lot of.”</p>
